:)</span><hr size=1> I wanted money... I got money, though in a kind of unusual way hehe. This is my story:<br>
<br>
As I was wandering BB I noticed 2 highlevel druid/ranger PC's kiting Delin Ironblend, killing it and only looting the money. So I decided to stay and hide myself and be a scavenger for a little while, looting the rest. It brought me 10 2H battleaxes and Necro words I sold for 25 pp a piece.<br>
<br>
But the best was yet to come!!<br>
<br>
I was rogue invis, one of them was meditating and the other was talking. when I noticed him dropping a book on the floor and I overheard him saying he got it from SOL A... and the other one shiuld take it as a present<br>
<br>
 I was immediatly interested hehe<br>
Still cautious, deciding what to do, he left to kite the dwarf again... leaving me with a book from a highlevel zone and a meditating (therefor blind) PC.<br>
<br>
I sneaked up to the book, took it and walked a little back to see what would happen and to check what the book is.<br>
I had robbed a BLACK TOME WITH SILVER RUNES from a player, that made my day since a guildmember told me it was worth about 600 pp hehehe<br>
<br>
The one attacking the dwarf died kiting it (what a loser) and the other was still meditating (they probably think the book was lost when the one dropping it zoned because he died hehe)<br>
<br>
I traded the book for elfhide gloves, jagged band dragoon dirk and 150 pp <br>
heheh not bad for a level 8 right? or was it even too low a trick for a rogue?? hehe I never regreted my decision, for I AM a rogue and whomever drops a 600 pp worth book on the floor deserves to lose it.<br>
<br>
